  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "An ***elegy*** is a [poem](../../../terms/poem.md) of mourning — a meditation on loss, death, or the passage of time. The elegy is one of the oldest poetic modes, traceable to Greek and Latin traditions, and one of the most enduring: the impulse to address the dead, to give shape to grief, and to find (or fail to find) consolation is as old as poetry itself.",
